&lt;p&gt;This means if your flex container is not wide enough (for flex-direction:row) or tall enough (for flex-direction:column) that your flex items will overflow the container.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Flex-direction:row&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Flex-direction:row will render only a single flex line on the horizontal axis. Rendering the flex items from left to right.&lt;/p&gt;
